\s1 The Beginning of Knowledge
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 1:1 \xt ch. 10:1; 25:1; 1 Kgs. 4:32; Eccles. 12:9\x*The proverbs of Solomon, son of David, king of Israel:
\b
\q1
\v 2 To know wisdom and instruction,
\q2 to understand words of insight,
\q1
\v 3 to receive instruction in wise dealing,
\q2 in \x + \xo 1:3 \xt ch. 2:9\x*righteousness, justice, and equity;
\q1
\v 4 to give prudence to \x + \xo 1:4 \xt ch. 8:5; 14:15, 18 \x*the simple,
\q2 knowledge and \x + \xo 1:4 \xt ch. 2:11; 3:21\x*discretion to the youth—
\q1
\v 5 Let the wise hear and \x + \xo 1:5 \xt ch. 9:9\x*increase in learning,
